<page api="xb" build="7661">
    <shortlink>xb curl_get_file function</shortlink>
    <topic>curl_get_file Function</topic>
    <description>
        <p>Downloads a file using CURL.</p>
    </description>
    <prototypes>
        <prototype>dim result as L = curl_get_file(url as C, filename as C)</prototype>
    </prototypes>
    <arguments>
        <argument>
            <name>url</name>
            <type>c</type>
            <description>
                <p>The URL where the file is stored.</p>
            </description>
        </argument>
        <argument>
            <name>filename</name>
            <type>c</type>
            <description>
                <p>The name of the file.</p>
            </description>
        </argument>
    </arguments>
    <returns>
        <return>
            <name>result</name>
            <type>L</type>
            <description>
                <p>Returns *[xb:.t.]* if the operation succeeds. Otherwise, *[xb:.f.]*.</p>
            </description>
        </return>
    </returns>
    <discussion>
        <p>The curl_get_file() function can be used to download a file from a remote location. The function uses CURL to download the file.</p>
    </discussion>
    <example code="xb"><![CDATA[result = curl_get_file("https://www.example.com/documents","myfile.pdf")]]></example>
    <see>
        <ref link=""></ref>
    </see>
</page>